Provisional and preliminary results for the Lake Okeechobee 2020/2021 sediment sampling conducted by University of Florida.

Sediment Zones

Sediment zones across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.


* Spatially interpolated using weighted k-nearest neighbor classifier with up to 10 nearest neighbots considered (i.e. k=10; kknn function in the kknn R-library).

Mud Depth

Mud depth across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling.


* Spatially using tension spline (Tps function in the fields R-library).

Total Phoshorus

Total phosphorus across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated TP concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

Model diagnostic plots

Total phosphorus krige model diagonistic plots including residual versus fitted (top left), QQplot (bottom left), scale-location (top right) and histogram of residuals (bottom right). Residuals are not significantly different from a normal distribution (Shapiro-Wilk; W=0.99, p value=0.42).

Inorganic Phoshorus (HCl TP)

  • Data was log-transformed prior to variogram fitting.
  • After kriging, the data were back-transformed consistent with Yamamoto (2007) and Journel (1980)

Comparison of original values, back-transformed and corrected back-transformed data.

Inorganic phosphorus (HCl extracted) across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated TP concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

Model diagnostic plots

Inorganic phosphorus (HCl extracted) krige model diagonistic plots including residual versus fitted (top left), QQplot (bottom left), scale-location (top right) and histogram of residuals (bottom right). Residuals are not significantly different from a normal distribution (Shapiro-Wilk; W=0.98, p value=0.09).

Inorganic Phoshorus (NaHCO3 Pi)

  • Data was log-transformed prior to variogram fitting.
  • After kriging, the data were back-transformed consistent with Yamamoto (2007) and Journel (1980)

Inorganic phosphorus (NaHCO₃ extracted) across Lake Okeechobee observed during the 2020/2021 sampling including (left) semivariogram, (center) interpolated TP concentrations and (right) 95% Confience Interval interpolation.

Model diagnostic plots

Inorganic phosphorus (NaHCO₃ extracted) krige model diagonistic plots including residual versus fitted (top left), QQplot (bottom left), scale-location (top right) and histogram of residuals (bottom right). Residuals are not significantly different from a normal distribution (Shapiro-Wilk; W=0.98, p value=0.07).
